            <outline text="Perfect abstract video">
                <outline text="How to Write the Perfect Abstract">
                    <outline text="Abstract">
                        <outline text="Being able to write a great abstract is a prerequisite for creating appealing articles, theses or papers. A good dissertation or research paper can often be recognised by the high quality of its abstract. However, it is notoriously difficult to create such a good abstract. Having a good methodology in place will help tremendously with this task. In this presentation, a methodology based on a specific, recommended structure will be explained."/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Motivation" colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="A good dissertation or research paper can often be recognised by the __quality of its abstract__." colorLabel="4"/>
                        <outline text="However, it is __notoriously difficult__ to create a very good abstract." colorLabel="4"/>
                        <outline text="Having a __good methodology__ in place will help tremendously." colorLabel="4"/>
                        <outline text="This will be explained in this presentation!" colorLabel="4"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="What is an abstract?" colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="An abstract is effectively a __condensed summary__ of your entire report or article."/>
                        <outline text="Different types of academic abstracts exist: ">
                            <outline text="__Thesis abstract__"/>
                            <outline text="__Paper abstract__"/>
                            <outline text="__Extended abstract__"/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="There is also an __Executive summary__."/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Structure matters!" colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="It is extremely important to have the __right structure__ in place."/>
                        <outline text="It helps in ensuring the __high quality__ of the abstract, and also helps with the __writing process__."/>
                        <outline text="My recommended structure:" colorLabel="4">
                            <outline text="[MOTIVATION] (1 sentence)"/>
                            <outline text="CONTEXT/BACKGROUND (2-3 sentences): 1/3 of abstract"/>
                            <outline text="CONTRIBUTION 2/3 of abstract"/>
                            <outline text="[CONCLUSION]"/>
                            <outline text="====="/>
                            <outline text="TOTAL: 100-150 words"/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Writing your abstract " colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="__When__ should you write the abstract?">
                            <outline text="Most of the time, at the end. But it can also be written at the beginning or in between."/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="__How__ should you write the abstract?">
                            <outline text="You should use plain text and a decent outlining tool such as Dynalist or WorkFlowy."/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="__How long will it take__ to write the abstract?">
                            <outline text="As it can take a considerable amount of time to write your abstract, you should work in iterations."/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Summary" colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="Being able to write a great abstract is a prerequisite for creating appealing articles, theses or papers." colorLabel="4"/>
                        <outline text="Different types of abstracts exist, we have focused on a simple academic abstract type."/>
                        <outline text="Dear into a well-defined structure is the essential ingredient in getting it right."/>
                        <outline text="You can write the abstract at different times, using different tools, but the main thing is to work in iterations."/>
                        <outline text="Homework: write an abstract for this talk! The solution will be given in the next video..."/>
                    </outline>
                </outline>
