            <outline text="Qatar Reading Group Talk 1 (June 2020)" _note="[https://www.overleaf.com/project/59f1d1c45cd281015b4d389a]">
                <outline text="Paper Proposal: A Game Theoretic Framework for Human-as-a-Sensor-Assisted Machine Learning"/>
                <outline text="Abstract #slide ">
                    <outline text="The proposed system is made up of a Machine learning algorithm that carries out a classification task [was: decides to either verify or trust $$N$$ users for which they might be adversary or not]."/>
                    <outline text="The classification process can also be done using a Wizard that might have a higher cost than using the ML algorithm but will classify with high accuracy."/>
                    <outline text="The goal of this work is to identify a mixed strategy between using the system or the Wizard [was: trusting and verifying the users] which is a best response Nash equilibrium."/>
                    <outline text="Multiple non critical applications can benefit from such a model including social media human verification systems."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="The ML System Model #slide  ">
                    <outline text="![system.png](https://www.dropbox.com/s/efus7p05bpcuuej/system.png?dl=1) #eyo-style:Normal"/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="ML Component #slide ">
                    <outline text="For each ML component $$ML_i$$ $$(i=1,\ldots n)$$ denote">
                        <outline text="$$c_i$$ -- running cost"/>
                        <outline text="$$R_i$$ -- reliability (probability of correct classification)"/>
                        <outline text="$$b_i$$ -- benefit (assume proportional to its reliability)"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="The component's utility is then $$u_i = c_i-b_i=c_i-\alpha R_i$$."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="Wizard Component #slide ">
                    <outline text="Similarly, for this component we have">
                        <outline text="$$c_W \gg c_i \;\forall i$$ -- running cost"/>
                        <outline text="$$R_W \gg R_i\;\forall i$$ -- reliability"/>
                        <outline text="$$b_W$$ -- benefit"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="We state $$u_W= c_W-b_W=c_W-\alpha R_W$$."/>
                </outline>
                <outline text="System Utility #slide ">
                    <outline text="The overall system reliability (using the first $$k$$ ML components) is ">
                        <outline text="$$R_S = \left\{\begin{array}{ll} 1-\prod_k(1-R_i), &amp;\text{ if Wizard is not used.}\\ R_W, &amp;\text{ otherwise.}\end{array}\right.$$"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="The system overall utility can be stated as">
                        <outline text="$$U_S= \left\{\begin{array}{ll} \alpha R_S - \sum_k c_i, &amp;\text{ if Wizard is not used.}\\ \alpha R_W- c_W, &amp;\text{ otherwise.}\end{array}\right.$$"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Potential goals: ">
                        <outline text="maximise $$R_S$$?"/>
                        <outline text="maximise $$U_S$$?"/>
                        <outline text="maximise $$U_S$$ and ensure $$R_S \ge t$$ where $$t$$ is a given threshold?"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="We seem to need some mathematical optimisation technique here."/>
                </outline>
